annotationA: Small ubiquitin-related modifier; Smt3 is the only Drosophila SUMO family protein. It is required for embryonic patterning and mitosis. It may also have roles in wing patterning, Dpp signaling, and Ras/MAPK signaling. It localizes to the nucleus during interphase  and to the kinetochores and midbodies during mitosis
annotationB: Nuclear pore complex protein Nup133; Probable component of the nuclear pore complex (NPC) (Probable). Plays a role in NPC assembly and/or maintenance
